@Conrad, I'm happy to assisting you get this committed if you are willing to provide feedback on the patch. As maintainer of the port and a committer, there's an expectation that we support not-yet-EoL FreeBSD releases.

The patch syntactically looks OK to me, and I have asked lightside to provide confirmation of successful builds on 10.1{i386,amd64} and 9.x{i386,amd64}

I can provide the ports commit approval if you're happy with its semantics.

Maintainer is Committer, assign accordingly
